inn1.comm: floated full on middle, Porterfield replies with a defensive push to mid-on
straying into the pads, hint of inswing for Wheal, neatly picked off to long leg off the back foot for a single
shorter and slanting in from over the stumps, Stirling prods to the leg side via an inside edge
Wheal hits an in-between length now - neither driveable nor pullable - dabbed to the leg side
on a length and outside off, Stirling drags himself forward and drives on the up to the left of mid-off

Wheal swoops in from his followthrough and clings onto a sharp return catch. He claims the catch and the finger goes up. He sends Stirling packing for a duck. This was an excellent delivery: a length ball that nips back in from outside off. Stirling presses forward to defend. Instead, he inside-edges it onto his thigh pad. The ball pops up, Wheal dives forward and snaffles it. Great reflexes shown by the bowler
worked off the pads through square leg
full and outside off, no shot
back of a length and nipping away outside off, skips past the outside edge
full and outside off, tapped into the covers off the front foot
full and running away outside off with the angle from over the wicket, Porterfield hangs his bat out and watches the ball beat the outside edge. The white thing is darting around under overcast skies
shorter and thuds into the top of the bat. The batsman did well to loosen his grip
full and outside off, presses forward and drives to cover

very full, and swinging in, Balbirnie plays around his front pad and is hit on the front pad below the knee-roll in line with middle. Umpire Wilson shoots down the appeal. That appeared very adjacent but Wilson perhaps thought it was heading down leg. Big reprieve for Balbirnie
full and straight, clipped through midwicket. Balbirnie passes 1000 runs in ODIs
full and outside off, no shot
full and angling into a push straight of mid-off. Excellent timing, and that's the first boundary of the match
tucked off the pads to fine leg
back of a length and outside off, ignored
full and outside off, left alone
shorter and outside off, gets on top of the bounce and punches to cover
back of a length and angling across off, ignored
yorker on off stump, jabbed back to the bowler
short and outside off, gets on top of the bounce and guides to backward point
back of a length and angling into a forward-defensive push
full and straight, bunted to the right of short midwicket
short and into the rib cage, Porterfield is beaten for pace and sends a top edge fluttering over long leg for a six
full and angling away outside off, left alone
back of a length on middle, defended
back of a length and outside off, reaches out for the ball and punches it through the gap at backward point
slightly overpitched and outside off, Balbirnie leans into it and caresses a cover drive
back of a length and zipping away outside off, left alone
back of a length on off, defended
shorter and skids off the pitch on middle, the batsman loosens his grip and blocks it back
back of a length on middle and leg, back-foot punch to mid-on
short at the body, pulled down to long leg
short and shoved down leg for a wide
back of a length and on the pads, whipped to long leg
full and outside off, no shot
shorter and outside off, throws his bat at the ball and chops it past the stumps to the left of the keeper
wide of the crease, angling in, and straightening away in the channel. Ignored
shorter but pushes it past the tramline. Off-side wide
back of a length and outside off, flashed into the covers
back of a length on middle, whipped to the leg side
good length and outside off, left alone
full and outside off, driven sweetly to the covers
full on middle, forward and driven to mid-on
full on middle, pushed back
back of a length on the hips, short-armed to deep square leg
full and angling away outside off, sliced off the outside half to point
overpitched and outside off, driven through the line to mid-off
forced off the back foot to midwicket
clipped with the angle to midwicket
wide of the crease, angling down the leg side, Balbirnie lets it go, the ball grazes the thigh pad and rolls away fine past the diving keeper for four
short at aimed the chest, he rides the bounce, rolls his wrists, and hooks to long leg
short and angling in at the top of off, fended off to the leg side
on a length and outside off, presses forward and tips it to cover
shorter and outside off, defended
full and floated outside off, left alone
swinging into the pads, shuffles across off, plays around his front pad, and squirts it to the right of midwicket
edged, but it did carry to Leask at first slip? This was nice and full outside off, bends away further, fetches the outside edge but, Leask drops a low catch to his right. It did carry to him
back of a length and outside off, goes back and flays it to cover
skids in on off, punched back to the bowler
wide of the crease, angling into a front-foot push to mid-on
dropped fractionally short and wide outside off, Porterfield finds his release. He frees his arms and slaps it fiercely to the left of short cover. No protection in the deep there

Balbirnie dishes out a full-length dive at the striker's end and that saves him. The throw wasn't great either - it was well over the head of the keeper. This was shortish and outside off as well, he rocks back and slaps it to short cover's right and sets off. Balbirnie sets off and makes his ground with the help of a poor throw and a full-length dive
arm ball, faster and quicker, defended to the off side
short of a length on off, jumps and keeps it out
same length, punched off the backfoot to the right of extra cover
good length on off, blocked
chopped on! Short of a length, not much room, Porterfield can't entirely open up as he attempts to punch it away
back of a length outside off, left alone
back of a length, tucked off the pads to the on side
full, pushed into the off side
short of a length, pitching outside leg, raps the pad as he misses the flick
back of a length, angled across, keeps his bat inside the line
jumps to a shortish one and keeps it out on the leg side
full, angled across more than a set of stumps outside off, driven through the covers
short of a length, shuffles and blocks down the pitch
short, gets on top and beats point and third man to their right with a backfoot punch
back of a length, shuffles and blocks
defended off the backfoot to mid-off
short, gets under it. Too high
short of a length, left alone outside off
back of a length, blocked
punches but can't find the gap past point
short, angling across him, he hooks off the top-edge against the angle and the ball lands on the bounce in front of deep backward square
tucked to the right of midwicket for a brace
short outside off, punched to cover
even shorter, this time he waits a little longer before carving it away past a diving point with an open face
short outside off, too high as he barely has to duck
gets on top of the bounce and pats it away to point
spinning in from a back of a length, tucked to deep backward square leg
fullish, spinning in, blocked
short and turning in, pulls with the spin to short fine who half-stops it with a dive
fullish outside off, tap and a run to cover
driven off the inside of the bat to mid-off
gets down to sweep and manages to contact
short of a length, tucked to midwicket
accurate and left alone
good length, blocked off the front foot
brilliant save by point as he flings himself to his right to intercept this cut
short, pulled from outside off, to deep backward square leg
gets slightly opened up by late movement as the ball trickles down to third man off the outside part of the bat
spinning away, defended into the covers
makes room and forces a punch through cover
gets down to sweep to the wrong length, not full enough at all. Got the front foot across, so seems like impact was outside off
tucked to midwicket
flloated up outside off, driven to cover
spinning in and turned away behind square
short outside off, uses the spin to whip it to deep midwicket
short of a length, stays in the crease and blocks
short, backs away and crunches to cover
short of a length, turning in, flicked to square leg
straight on a length, defended
sliding in on leg, clipped to midwicket
pitched up on middle and leg, clipped to midwicket
sweeps a length ball from outside off and the ball turns in to find the inside edge and trickle to fine leg
same length, tries to repeat the stroke and the ball drifts down to get past it
blocked towards mid-on
length, tucked to square leg
blocked off the front foot
full on middle, rolls his wrists and sweeps a couple to long leg
non-turner on a fourth-stump line, pushed to the off side off the front foot
tossed on off, bends forward and smothers any turn
shorter and outside off, forced off the back foot to extra cover
back of a length and sliding into the hips, Balbirnie stands tall, clips it to McLeod at midwicket and beats the direct hit at the non-striker's end
flatter and outside off, carved away to the off-side sweeper

looped up invitingly outside off, Balbirnie stretches out and smoothly drives it to extra cover, where the fielder fumbles and allows a single. Balbirnie brings up his fifty off 78 balls. A fifty after scores of 7,9,7,2 earlier in the tournament
on a length and outside off, dabbed to point
rides the bounce and plays to point
full, straight, worked to midwicket
Niall O'Brien ventures forward and runs it gently to backward point
tossed outside off, forward and driven to cover
pushed to short midwicket off the front foot
drifts in, dabbed to short midwicket again, this time from the crease
tucked off the pads to square leg, where Wallace dives to his right to stop the ball
shorter on middle, punched away to the leg side
non-turner outside off, punched away, this time to long-off off the front foot
dangled up on middle, Niall pats it to the covers
short and spins away outside off, he sends an airy drive between point and cover
opens the face and defends to short cover
swept from off stump to deep square leg
tossed outside off, Niall now employs the sweep. He drags it from outside off to the square-leg boundary. That strike brings up the fifty stand between him and Balbirnie
presses forward and runs it away to point
he dabs another floaty offbreak to point
Balbirnie plays around his front pad and flicks a full offering from middle stump to short midwicket
back of a length and angling into a solid punch to deep midwicket
leg-stump ball, which is glanced away behind square
overpitched and outside off, driven to the right of the bowler and left of mid-on
jabbed back to Berrington
half-volley outside off, drilled to the left of sweeper cover
clipped with the break to deep midwicket
swept from outside off to deep midwicket
swept with the spin to the right of deep square leg
tossed on middle, driven down the ground
tight lines, forward and smothered
rides the bounce of this short ball outside off and chops it away
full and straight, whipped to deep midwicket
back of a length and outside off, angled to third man
full and on middle, driven to the right of mid-on
full and attacking middle, Niall covers up in defence
full and nips back in to beat the inside edge and strike the front pad but this is heading past leg stump
short and wide, stabbed away to deep cover
full and outside off, flashes an outside edge and sends the ball fine of deep third man
full on middle, played back to the bowler
Niall leans back and punches this back-of-a-length ball from outside off to sweeper cover
Balbirnie reaches out for this short ball outside off and flays it to third man
clipped off the pads to short midwicket
on the pads again, glanced to fine leg. Niall hares back for the second
Balbirnie stretches out and plays it back to the bowler
nudged with the spin to square leg
tossed on middle, tip and run to cover
darted outside off, smeared to deep cover off the front foot
clipped to deep midwicket for one more
straight ball on middle, tapped to long-on
full and wide outside off, Balbirnie slices an outside edge to third man
short and outside off, bounces over the top edge, as he cuts and misses
gets on top of a short one outside off and punches to backward point
Niall runs down the track, slogs to the leg side, and only collects fresh air
floated full on off, driven to the left of mid-on off the front foot
Sharif founds extra bounce from a length to beat the cut
leg-side wide
turned with the spin to the right of midwicket
paddled from outside off, gets enough bat to beat the chase of short fine leg, and fetch a boundary
pushed down the leg side, brings out the flat, hard sweep. Crunched over square leg
full on the stumps, hit down to long-on
slides on outside off, tapped to the off side
eased to long-on off the front foot
short and lifting at the head, top-edges a hook fine of long leg
back of a length and outside off, punched to the right of backward point
overpitched and outside off, belted away to the right of the bowler and left of mid-on. Niall O'Brien brings up a fifty of his own in emphatic fashion
tucked around the corner
full on middle, pushed to mid-off
closes the bat-face and squeezes a full ball on middle to mid-on
flighted on off, forward and driven to long-on
wide of the crease, angling in on middle, forced to long-on
clipped to the left of midwicket now
driven through the line to long-off. Leask runs in from long-off and lets the ball burst through his hands to the boundary
back of a length and angling down leg from around the wicket. Re-set the radar, Sole
short on leg stump, swatted away to long leg
dug in short and outside off, dragged across the line to midwicket
short on the chest, rides the bounce and pulls it away fine of long leg. Good execution of the pull
on a length and outside off, punched up to the covers
back of a length on off, cramps the batsman for room, chopped to short third man
backs away and squirts an inside edge to midwicket
jabbed to midwicket again
floated up on middle, eased down to long-on
tossed outside off, steps down the track, but does not get close enough to the pitch. So, he ends up slicing a loft over extra cover
drilled from outside off to long-off
swept from the stumps to deep square leg
back of a length on off, defended to cover
on a length and outside off, Balbirnie lets it slide off the face to backward point
Balbirnie rises on top of a short ball outside off and flays it in the air to the right of backward point and beats third man in the deep too
back of a length and outside off, carved to third man
pitches outside leg and swings away to hit the pad
Niall is cramped up for room. He chops an inside edge onto his boot and that's drinks
tossed on a fourth-stump line, Balbirnie presses forward and gently drops the ball to the cover-point region. He then hares across to the other end. Good urgency
slower through the air and outside off, Niall drags the ball from there and firmly sweeps it square of short fine leg
shorter offbreak outside off, cracked with the turn to sweeper cover
flatter and faster, turns in, Balbirnie ventures deep in the crease and defends it to the leg side
floated up outside off, Balbirnie stretches out for an ambitious reverse-sweep and misses
Balbirnie uses his feet, Leask shortens his length and shifts his line to the stumps to keep the batsman to a quiet defence

Niall falls to a mix-up between the wickets. Back of a length on the leg stump, Wheal tucks up the batsman for room. Niall adjusts and works the ball more or less straight to Wallace at short midwicket. He aims for a non-existent single. He takes a couple of paces forward, then stops, he re-starts but knows he has no chance of making the crease. Good work from Wallace: he swooped down on the ball and effected a direct hit at the non-striker's end. Niall wasn't even in the frame
back of a length and angling in on middle, punched to midwicket
stands tall and punches to short cover
guided to backward point
short, wide, scythed to sweeper cover
full on off, pushed to the off side
short, wide, slashed to cover
turned to the leg side
swept to short fine
hacked to the covers
shorter, wider, he latches onto the width and cracks it away past backward point
punched to midwicket
good length on off, defended
full, wide, slashes at it and beats backward point to his right
short around off, ample room available to free up the arms and he carts a pull over deep midwicket
slower full ball outside off, pushed back
closer this time but too short and Kevin O'Brien rocks back and latches onto a pull over deep square leg
slower full ball, wide and drifts away further to beat the flashing blade
fullish length on middle and leg, pushed back
short, wide, backs away and carves a cut to the left of deep cover who runs across and dives but the ball beats him
length ball on middle and off, stays back and punches
sliding fuller one on leg, driven back

loops it up outside leg and he sweeps to deep fine leg. Beats Wheal who pushes it back but makes contact with the ropes when his left hand touches the ball inadvertently as he tries to take it off. Ah, hang on. No, it seems like he's just done fine. Not given a four
punched back
closes the face looking for a flick across the line but this length ball straightens and beats the bat and misses off-stump narrowly
good length outside off, deftly guided to third man off the outside part of the bat
length outside off, drops it into the covers
fullish length, pushed through cover
pushes away from the body and gets an outside edge to third man
leg-side slider, down on one knee and swept to fine leg
pitched up outside off, pushed to long-off
flicks with the angle to midwicket and jogs the single to raise his hundred. Crucial that he stays on and finishes off the job
fuller on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
full on leg, pushed towards midwicket
drifts down the leg side
back of a length, punched back
back of a length, tries to flick and gets a glove to the pad
shortish and flat, rocks back and flays a pull well over deep midwicket
short of a length, makes room and punches to cover
fullish, too much room, and he tries to slap it straight over. But the excess width means he needed to move closer as this one lobs in the air off the bottom of the bat
shovelled to wide long-off
attempted reverse sweep, no contact
short, outside off, drops it to point and takes off
full outside off, carved through point
gets down to sweep and gets a top-edge to fine leg
comes down the ground to flay it to sweeper cover
full, angling on leg, worked to long-on
misses the reverse sweep and is struck on the pad. The umpire raises his finger. Curving in towards off and pinning him
short of a length outside off, opens the face and guides to point
gets the front foot forward ans pushes through cover
was that a catch?Great effort, short of a length, outside off, Kevin short-arm jabs this to the right of backward square leg who runs across and sticks the hand out but the ball gets out
gone! This time he's picked out the fielder. It was on a fuller length and Kevin pushes away from the body to find the outside edge and be caught at gully
short of a length. flicked behind square
slower full ball outside off, 119ks, pushed into the off side
dipping fuller ball, tries to clip and the ball slides in to hit the pad. Would have missed the leg stump
slower fullish one, punched to long-off
short of a length, opens the face to short third man
short of a length, down the leg side
short and wide, punched to wide long-off
fulller, clipped to midwicket
gets down and across for a paddle and gets a leading edge to square leg
short of a length, pulled through midwicket and mid-on, and takes off for a single. Beats the throw from the deep towards the bowler's end with a dive
full, angling in on the pads, clipped to short fine leg
slower ball, worked through mid-off
full, wide, squeezed through point
gets down on one knee and tries to scoop this but it's slower and not full enough, and it cuts in to take the top of leg stump
good length, flicked to square leg
walks forward to meet the pitch and thinks of a second after flicking but long-on runs forward and tidies up
full, wide, backs away and carves it away to point
full on middle and off, driven out to long-off
high full toss, slips out of the hand, no call from the umpire as the batsman swings and misses
full, angled across, driven to mid-off
full outside off, crunches it over the in-field at the point region
picks a full toss to hole out to long-on. Catching practice for the man there as he does not have to move an inch. Flayed into his hands from the crease
walks across and tries to paddle one fine but the line is too straight and the length not full enough
full, angling across off, clears the front leg and slashes over extra cover. Rankin tries to go for the extra run but McBrine is least interested and sends him back. Loses his wicket for his troubles

inn2.comm: starts off with a 109ks slower, short ball outside off. Cross waits for the ball to arrive and dabs to point with soft hands
offcutter, back of a length, curves back in, beats the inside edge and hits the thigh
much fuller and angling into a front-foot push back to Murtagh
115ks, back of a length, nipping in, fetches the inside edge. The ball wanders away to the midwicket region
back of a length and on off, Cross deploys a solid stride and pushes the ball defensively to mid-on
another floaty offcutter, comes back in from outside off, Cross does not pick the variation. He wears it on the thigh pad
starts off with a sharp chest-high short ball on middle stump, the batsman rides the bounce and controls a hook to deep square leg
back of a length and outside off, stays leg-side of the ball and belts it to extra cover
back of a length and outside off, jabbed off the inside half to midwicket
full and wide outside off, the batsman throws his bat at the ball.... and misses
full and just a shade outside off, squirted to midwicket
back of a length and outside off, flashes and collects fresh air again
back of a length and outside off, crisply punches through the covers and watches the ball purr away to the boundary. Quality shot
full and angling in, poked to cover off a leading edge
full and outside off, presses forward and caresses through the covers
back of a length and angling in on middle, defended
on a length on off, guides it to the covers
back of a length and skidding into leg stump, off the pad to square leg
on a length, seams away, bounces past the outside edge
back of a length and outside off, punched up to cover-point
full and outside off, swings away, drives away from the body and misses
shorter and much wider outside off, Cross chases after it and does not make contact
steps down the track and hacks an inside edge to fine leg
short and wide, he frees his arms and flashes it over backward point
full and outside off, chips a drive to the left of short cover
gets on top of a shortish ball outside off and punches to mid-off
Coetzer swishes and misses outside off
on a length and outside off, beats the outside edge again
back of a length and angling into a regal punch straight of mid-off
rides the bounce of this short one outside off and glides to third man
short, wide, reaches out for the ball with his hands and scythes it away past the reach of backward point as well as third man in the deep
back of a length and outside off, gets behind the line and defends
full and nipping down leg, deflected behind to the keeper off the pad

Murtagh provides Ireland with the breakthrough. Wilson throws himself to his left from first slip and snags an excellent catch. This was a good length ball put a shade outside off, nips away, Cross aims for a leg-side slog. He can only send a thick outside edge behind
full outside off, left alone
presses forward and pushes a full ball to mid-on
short, outside off, punched up to cover
full and outside off, toe-ends a drive to mid-off
driven on the up but straight to mid-off. Murtagh rounds out a wicket-maiden
back of a length on off, Coetzer greets him into the attack with a punched four. The ball hurtles away to the long-off fence
back of a length and skidding into the body, turned to square leg
rises on top of a short ball outside off and ramps it up and over the slip fielder. Deftly done
back of a length, angling in, straightening away past the outside edge. The batsman was squared up and beaten
fended back down the pitch. Heavy ball from Rankin
gets on top of a back of a length ball outside off and punches on the up and through the covers. Coetzer takes three fours off Rankin's first over
good length on off, kept out
driven off the front foot but straight to cover
slower cutter, dropped beside the pitch
back of a length on off, shimmies out and defends it back
shimmies out and drives to mid-on
tipped to cover. Third maiden for Murtagh
short and keeps angling in to the batsman, who hops, skips, and fends it off
punched through the line to mid-off
short, wide, gets on top of the bounce and scythes it over backward point
back of a length and outside off, jumps on top of the bounce and flays it up and over extra cover
crunched through the covers for a hat-trick of boundaries
sliced off an outside edge to backward point
short of a length outside off, taps away to sweeper cover
short of a length, punched off the backfoot through point
back of a length, drifting down the leg side
just back of a length, defended off the front foot
short of a length on middle and leg, tucked away to deep backward square leg
that's an outrageous shot. Steps down the track despite it being short of a length and just presents the full face to chip it straight over cow corner
now the bowler switches to a fuller length and he again chips it over with the straightest of bats. This time, though, the ball is pulled back, just within centimeters from the ropes
short of a length, spinning in, tucked to the left of midwicket
back of a length, spinning in, punched towards long-on
short of a length, stands tall and punches off the backfoot towards mid-on
shifts back and across and tucks but can't beat mid-on's right
ah, mid on's just throwing himself around for everything. Now he runs forward to his left and dives to intercept a punch. Gary Wilson the fielder
flicked away for a single
accurate on off, defended
keeps a little low around leg stump, flicks with the angle past mid-on
full, drifting down the leg side
back of a length, defended off the inside of the bat
in the blockhole around middle, dug out straight down
full, sliding into middle and leg, punched to midwicket

dropped. Would have been a really, really catch. Coetzer stood legside of this wide fuller ball, and as a result, his attempt to heave it over results in an outside edge that lobs towards third man. Rankin runs forward and dives. The ball just about carries and he had to bend really low. Just can't get his hands entirely around it
full on middle, flicked away
pitched up outside off, fetches a sweep to deep backward square leg
length ball, spinning in on middle, stands tall and blocks to midwicket
pulls this shortish one away with the spin to deep midwicket
caught on both feet, shifts back late and knocks back off the outside of the bat
back of a length, keeps low, defended to cover
short of a length on off, jumps back and defends
short, wide, cut past the left of point but can't beat sweeper sprinting across
short of a length around off, forces a pull off the bottom of the bat to midwicket
flicked off the pads through midwicket, fielder in the deep cuts it off after moving to his left
full, around a set of stumps outside off, driven to sweeper cover
floated up around off, gets down and sweeps to deep square leg
back of a length, spinning towards off, defended back
spinning in and finding the inside of the bat as he plays at it with no feet
full and accurate, blocked back
spinning into the pads, flicked to deep square leg
tries to sweep a non-turner outside off and misses
defends a length ball down the pitch
pitched up on the stumps, blocked
non-turner, he closes the face expecting turn and skews it off the outside of the bat through point
in the aiiir, well over. Gets down to sweep and gets a big top-edge but the ball goes past the outstretched hands of deep backward square leg
defended back
length on off, blocked to the bowler
full on the stumps, defended back
comes forward and plays and the ball goes through midwicket off the inside of the bat. Brings up Coetzer's fifty
back of a length, punched past diving mid-on
pats it away to midwicket off the front foot
defended back to the bowler
stays in the crease and punches to long-on
gets down to sweep a length ball and finds short fine leg
tossed up on off, uses the angle to drill it down to long-on
just back of a length, just waits for it before playing the reverse sweep really late to get it through third man

has he taken that? Yes, the fielder seems confident. This time the sweep goes right off the middle of the bat, and that is why it goes straight into the hands of the fielder. A top-edge might have carried it over. The eccentricities of cricket. Balbirnie takes it reverse-cupped, moves back and to his left with the momentum and ends up doing a fine balancing act in front of the square leg boundary. They confirm upstairs and it's fine
pushes back to the left of the bowler
tossed up outside off, tight front-foot defence
fetches a sweep from outside off and mistimes it to short fine leg
too full, can't get underneath it entirely and he drills off the inside of the bat to long-on
defended back to the bowler
pitched up on middle, flicked towards midwicket
full on off, driven to mid-off
Niall goes up for a catch. Not out says the umpire. No wide signal as well, so that must have brushed the pad as he tried to flick and missed

flighted outside off, drilled back. Niall is again excited and goes up for a catch. The bowler himself only follows suit. They refer it upstairs. Soft signal is not out. Clearly bounces as soon as he makes contact. A time-wasting appeal. He smiles broadly in the end
short of a length, punched to long-on
stays back and works to midwicket
short of a length, spinning in on middle, defended down the pitch
nudged away towards midwicket
flighted outside off, inviting him to go over the top, and he does as he clears mid-off
full on middle and leg, clipped behind square
crunches a sweep from middle and off to backward square leg
flicked with the turn to deep midwicket
tossed up and dipping on middle and leg, driven back to the bowler who gets a hand diving
trickled away with the angle and spin through fine leg
pitched up on off, pushed down the ground
pushed through the covers
full on leg, pushed to mid-on
waits and opens the face to third man

edged and taken. Slashes at a back of a length delivery that nips away without any feet and gets a healthy outside edge that Niall dives to his left to snaffle. Four down. Scotland's chase getting harder
on the pads, flicked uppishly through square leg
short of a length, gets beaten as he sticks the bat out

that's an awful way to get out. Catch practice for the bowler who's been gift-wrapped a wicket. Backs away early and Rankin follows him and drags the length back. He awkwardly slaps it back without being able to free his arms and can only get it as far as into the hands of the bowler
short of a length, punched to cover off the backfoot
short, gets well over the attempted pull. Niall does well to jump and gather it

he's holed out here. Leaks advances down the ground and it seems as though he's got to the pitch of this but ends up carving it straight over off the bottom of the bat. Long-on moves to his left and snaffles it

almost chips a catch back. Advances and pushes a scrambled-seam delivery back to the bowler. Just bounces in front of him as he bends to grab it

length ball on off or just a shade outside off, right in the swinging arc of Berrington. He slog-sweeps a six over midwicket. Bam!
pretty full and on off, forced down to long-on for a single

Murtagh knocks out Berrington's off stump. This was not short enough for a pull and the line is on off. Berrington still goes for a pull and loses his off stump. Berrington goes and with it Scotland's hopes?
Watt pushes outside off and squirts an outside edge to third man

straying into the hips, duly glanced to fine leg

flat-batted to mid-off

another slower ball, guided to the right of sweeper. Scotland reach 200
McCarthy deceives Sharif with a slower ball from the back of the hand. Sharif does not read the change-up. He slogs early and loses his off stump

McCarthy has Sole caught behind. The batsman dares to step down the track. McCarthy pulls his length back. Sole hangs his periscope up and gives a catch to the keeper

swings hard and inside-edges the ball onto his pad. They hare across for a single. Murtagh swoops in and kicks the ball onto the stumps but Wheal is in

Ireland keep their World Cup hopes alive! Back of a length on off, Rankin bowls a heavy ball. Wheal backs away again for a biiiig slog. He only snicks it behind. Niall throws himself to his right, and clings onto the one-handed catch to wrap things up for Ireland
